<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR AND
        COMPONENT REMOVal - CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPES</title>
        <para>Charge air cooler pipes and clamps (
            <hotlnk document="s12008_2.xml" xrefid="f1200801">Items 4 and 5, Figure 1</hotlnk>) are located on the upper
            radiator section.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200810" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200810.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200810.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 10. Charge Air Cooler Connections (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UPPER RADIATOR FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR MOUNTING BLOCK AND BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. TENSION SPRING CLAMP</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prior to removing or disconnecting the charge air cooler pipes, locate the air conditioning
                condenser and condenser mounting brackets on the front side of the radiator assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the upper and lower condenser mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and secure the condenser in a location where it will not be damaged or the condenser
                lines kinked.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the tension spring clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200810">Item 3, Figure 10</hotlnk>), loosen, and remove clamp (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200811">Item 1, Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200811" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200811.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200811.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Charge Air Cooler Connection</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TENSION SPRING CLAMP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER CONNECTOR HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove charge air cooler connection hose from charge air cooler fitting connection.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure for driver side charge air cooler (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200812">Figure 12</hotlnk>) connection.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200812" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200812.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200812.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="272px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Driver Side Tension Spring Clamp Removal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
